cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses distributed complex event processing and parallel processing of operator instances, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of sliding windows and event correlation, which are fundamental data structures and algorithms used in complex event processing. 
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the design and implementation of a model-based batch scheduling controller, which is a software engineering solution to the problem of minimizing communication overhead. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the trade-off between processing load and communication overhead, which is a systems and control problem. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the reduction of communication overhead, which is a networking problem.
